1. Player Character Sheet – “Jetty”

1.1 Core Data

Field	Value
Name	Jetty
Role	Player character
Base Size	32×32 px (standing)
Hitbox	20×28 px centered, starting ~2 px above feet
Anchor/Pivot	Bottom-center (for precise platform contact)
Art Style	Pixel-art, soft colors, clear silhouette
Theme Variants	Same Jetty across all levels; minor palette tweaks optional


⸻

1.2 Animation Set

Animation	Frames	Frame Size	FPS (Target)	Loop	Notes
idle	4	32×32	6	Yes	Gentle hover/bob; tiny jetpack flicker
run	6	32×32	10–12	Yes	Leaning slightly forward, swinging arms
jetpack_thrust	6	32×32	12	Yes	Flames + smoke particles under backpack
jump_start	2	32×32	8	No	Brief pose when initial thrust starts
fall	2	32×32	6	Yes	Slightly panicked pose, body angled downward
hurt	3	32×32	10	No	Knockback pose; optional blink/red flash
death	5	32×32	10	No	Spin/fall apart or fade-out with sparkles
enter_door	3	32×32	8	No	Walk into doorway and fade/disappear

Suggested sprite file naming:
	•	Atlas: characters_jetty.png
	•	Animation regions (logical names for code):
	•	jetty_idle
	•	jetty_run
	•	jetty_jetpack
	•	jetty_jump_start
	•	jetty_fall
	•	jetty_hurt
	•	jetty_death
	•	jetty_enter_door

